  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nSession focused on creating a Request Optimizer skill using /skill-creator framework. The skill transforms vague user requests into structured, safer, cost-effective, and more actionable instructions for Manus. Comprehensive testing demonstrated successful optimization of an app delivery request from vague to detailed 6-phase testing workflow.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nUser wanted to create a skill that automatically improves requests to Manus by making them safer, less expensive, auto-executable, and better structured. Specific focus on app development change requests and general task optimization.\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nCreated Request Optimizer skill through collaborative design process. Identified 6 core optimization patterns: risk reduction, cost optimization, auto-execution enablement, structure enhancement, app development changes, and variant suggestion. Successfully tested the skill on sample app delivery request.\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [skill] Request Optimizer — AI skill that transforms vague requests into structured, actionable workflows\n- [demonstration] App Testing Optimization — 6-phase comprehensive testing workflow for app delivery\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Scope skill to cover both general tasks and specific app development workflows\n- Include cascade awareness for app changes (features → translations → styling)\n- Implement 6 core optimization patterns with specific transformation rules\n- Structure output with clear phases, checklists, and success criteria\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Collaborative skill design process with iterative refinement\n- Clear identification of transformation patterns\n- Practical testing with real-world example\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Request optimization can dramatically improve task clarity and safety\n- App development requests need special handling for dependency sequencing\n- Vague requests often hide complex multi-phase workflows\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- How to automatically detect when a request needs optimization vs direct execution\n- Integration patterns for seamless request preprocessing\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- Deploy Request Optimizer skill to skills library\n- Test with various request types to validate optimization patterns\n- Refine transformation rules based on usage patterns\n---\nUID: LVReXFIDZHeYLFkI43LKxi | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0203\n"
